# UploadM8 core

Read `AGENTS.md` and `routers/README.md` before structural changes.

## Architecture

- `app.py` — lifespan, middleware, `include_router` only. No new business handlers here.
- `routers/*.py` — thin HTTP handlers; call `services/` and `core/`.
- `services/`, `core/` — business logic, DB, shared helpers.
- `worker.py` + `stages/` — async upload pipeline (transcode, captions, publish).
- `frontend/` — static HTML/JS; API via `js/api-base.js` + `auth-stack.js`.
- `migrations/runtime_migrations.py` — single migration source of truth.

## Dual-repo deploy

- Backend scope → `sosswced/uploadm8-auth` (use `uploadm8-backend-push` skill).
- Frontend scope → `sosswced/uploadm8-frontend` (use `uploadm8-frontend-push` skill).
- Never `git add .` for backend push — stage scoped paths only.

## Agent safety

- Never commit `.env`, credentials, tokens, or `__pycache__`.
- Never `git push --force` to `main`/`master` unless user explicitly requests.
- Commit only when user explicitly asks.
- After backend edits: `python run_tests.py unit`. After frontend edits: `python run_tests.py frontend-lint`.
